cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the optimization of convolutional neural networks for computer vision applications, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of alternative formulations to the convolution operation and quantization are also discussed, which could fall under the algorithms (cs.AL) or computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a neural architecture search framework, which could be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
